Indonesia Stocks: Bakrie Sumatera, Bumi Minerals, Medco Energi

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-06-10T09:29:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/indonesia-stocks-bukit-asam-inco-medco-energi-internasional.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  dropped 18.54 points, or 0.5
percent, to 3,787.65, falling for a third day. The measure fell
1.5 percent this week, the most since the week ended Feb. 25  Palm oil producers: PT Perusahaan Perkebunan London Sumatra
Indonesia (LSIP IJ), the nation’s third-largest plantation stock
by market value, lost 1.1 percent to 2,350 rupiah. PT Bakrie
Sumatera Plantations (UNSP IJ) fell 2.1 percent to 460 rupiah,
the most since May 30. Palm oil futures declined for a fifth
day, losing as much as 1.7 percent to 3,231 ringgit ($1,070) a
metric ton in  Kuala Lumpur .  PT Bumi Resources Minerals (BRMS IJ), an Indonesian mining
company, sank 5.1 percent to 750 rupiah, the sharpest drop since
its Dec. 9 trading debut. The stock fell on speculation a 13
percent, three-day rally was excessive, according to Edwin
Sinaga, president director at PT FinanCorpindo Nusa, a Jakarta-
based brokerage. Bumi Minerals’ 14-day relative-strength index,
which measures how rapidly prices have advanced or dropped
during a specified period, rose to 79 yesterday. A reading of
more than 70 suggests to some analysts that the stock is poised
to fall.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, climbed 1 percent to 2,500 rupiah,
the first gain in six days. Medco received $35 million as a
settlement for receivables after selling drilling company PT
Apexindo Pratama Duta to PT Mitra International Resources in
2008, Medco said. Mitra originally owed Medco $68.2 million in
the form of guaranteed secured bonds as part of the A$340.89
million ($362 million) payment for buying Apexindo, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
